<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-4193] Lower the default maxReadBufferBytes for non-blocking servers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4193</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;AbstractNonblockingServerArgs&lt;/tt&gt; sets the default maximum read buffer size to &lt;tt&gt;Long.MAX_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt;. Almost every machine will probably OOME before it succeeds in hitting that maximum. It should have a lower maximum, perhaps 256 MB like the maximum frame size in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/master/lib/cpp/src/thrift/server/TNonblockingServer.h#L128&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;the cpp implementation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
